      <workgroup>Domain Name System Operations</workgroup>
      <keyword>DNS caching</keyword>
      <keyword>root zone</keyword>
      <abstract>
        <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes the queries that a DNS resolver should emit to initialize its cache. The result is that the resolver gets both a current NS resource record set (RRset) for the root zone and the necessary address information for reaching the root servers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This document obsoletes RFC 8109.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
